args:
Nameless is revealed to be Seimei. When
Elisanne learns the tournament prize mirror is a
memento of his late grandfather, her resolve
wavers, and she is defeated. Luca faces Seimei
next, promising to share his winnings with Elly.
Round Three, Fourth Match\nYoshitsune VS Elisanne
Victory will be mine, no matter what!\nHAAAAAH!
Match four's turned into a white-hot volley\nof blows, folks, and neither fighter's giving\nan inch against the other's onslaught!
You're a fiery one, girl! That's a mean\nthrust. I can feel your hunger for the win\nwith every attack!
But I'm not letting you have this till\nI've enjoyed my fill! Final exam time.\nWeave that spear of yours through THIS!
They've kicked things up another notch!\nIt looks as if Yoshitsune plans to unveil\nher ace in the hole!
Wha—the very air is a minefield! How am\nI meant to weave ANYTHING through this?
That's right... Losing isn't an option here.\nIf I can't avoid it, I'll meet it head-on!
If you wish to end this now, so be it!\nRAAAGH!
She's clinched it! She's turned back her\nopponent's technique with an astonishing\ndisplay of her own to seize the win!
You did. I felt the bite of your spear at my\nthroat. And now it seems I have a promise\nto uphold.
You've earned your prize. Here is how\nour nameless friend's technique can be\nundone.
Broadly speaking, you have two options.\nOne, overwhelm him with attacks to stop\nhim from using it. Two, avert your eyes.
You would have me look away mid-fight?
If you wish to win, yes. Those who lost no\nsooner than their matches had begun were\nall staring him square in the face.
I suspect he's using a linguistic spell\nbased on the phrase ＂hidden in plain\nsight＂ to conceal his true methods.
You say ＂true methods＂ like you know\nthis Nameless duder's real identity.\nYou even said ＂he.＂
Call it an old girl's intuition! I've seen a lot\nmore than you little sprouts in my years.
Still, I've told you no lies. Whether you\nbelieve me or not is entirely up to you.
That'll do it for me. I'd like to watch your\nnext matches over a nice plate of mochi,\nI think!
And there she goes.\nWhat do you all make of her words?
Hm. Now that she's mentioned it, I do\nrecall facing down my opponent head-on.
And I was starin' at his hands 'n feet.\nCan't say I really bothered with his face.\nMaybe that's what bought me time?
I see. Then perhaps it bears believing.\nFrankly, I have no option besides trusting\nwhat she claims.
Right. All that's left now is to get into the\nring with him and find out. Looks like the\nnext one to face him is, uh...
Me. And I intend to give it my all.\nSee you in the finals, Luca.
It's a date. Give 'im hell, Elisanne!
Round Four, First Match\nElisanne VS Nameless
Ohhh boy, here we go... I'm sweating tiny\nwaterfalls, and it's not even me up to bat!\nI hope she's got this.
Guy's gettin' more fans by the round.\nGuess I can't blame 'em, though, the\nway he's kickin' butts. Mine included.
We've made it to round four, and it's\nElisanne who makes the first move!\nShe's taken to the sky for a graceful dive!
But Nameless slips away from her spear!\nAnd here comes the shockwave counter!
Tch. I suspected as much. But if I don't\nmeet his gaze, it's no problem! Raaaaah!
Elisanne's laying the pressure on thick!\nWill she be the one to end Nameless's\nhot streak?!
Oh no! Is she paralyzed?!\nThat dirty cheater with his dirty tricks!
It looks like the tables have turned once\nagain, folks! If she can't break loose,\nElisanne's shot at victory ends here!
That technique... This will be more than\na matter of merely ＂breaking loose.＂\nIt will likely prove deadly.
The fight, er... The fight goes to...
Huh? Seimei is...running into the ring?
Have you lost your dang mind?! Who gives\ntwo hoots if ya win—you got any idea\nwhat that technique'll DO to a fella?!
What?! Seimei, why are you—\nWait, stop! The match will be have\nto be called off if the judge intercedes!
And since when do you speak like that?\nReally, what in the world is going on?!
Keep your fool mouth shut, fox.
Don't make a fool of yourself while you're\nwearing my face, you absolute moron.
Tsk. You've gone and ruined everything.\nWell? Are you satisfied, you utter dolt?
Ladies and gents, this is...unexpected!\nFirst we had one Seimei charge the stage,\nand now there are two of him!
So wait, Nameless was the guy running\nthis event the whole time?
Ah! Then the one behaving strangely must\nbe...
But this is your fault too, y'know.\nI can't believe you were gonna bust\nout a move that dangerous!

SWEET MOTHER OF MOCHI!
Seimei turned into Kuzunoha!
Wait, so she's been playing MC while
transformed into him this whole time?
Meanwhile, the real Seimei snuck into\nthe entrant pool as an anonymous fighter.\nBut why bother with such a farce?
Because. Even I have\nthings I can't let go of.
Sooo, uh, yeah... I only learned this after\nthe fact, but Yura's reflecting mirror's a\nsuper important memento to Seimei.
Amaterasu gifted it to a previous Ox\nclan leader, so to him, it's chock full\nof memories of his late grandpa.
He didn't want to give it up, but there\nwas no way he could disobey orders from\nup top in front of all the other clan heads.
I...see.\nSo it's a keepsake of a lost loved one.
Stop running your mouth, fox. *sigh*\nFine. If the jig is up, I'm out. I forfeit.
No. Please continue the match,\nLord Seimei.
How could I? True, it stings to lose those\nmemories, but continuing now, like this...\nConsider the optics here.
If you'll forgive me for saying so, maybe\nyou should actually listen to what the\npeople think, rather than assuming.
Yeaaaah! You've come this far, Nameless!\nBring it home! Let's see that win!
See? The crowd's dyin' to watch this fight.\nI'm sure Amaterasu'll let ya off the hook!
Unbelievable. Well...I suppose turning tail\nat this point would be even MORE\nhumiliating, in its own way.
Let's get back to it, Elisanne. I'll give\nyou time to brace for impact, at least.\nAnd, er...it's nothing personal.
Yo, watch out!\nHe's planning something big!
I wonder... Would it even be right to rob\nsomeone of such a precious keepsake?
O that which shines as the sun!\nI beseech you, release your flame\nand make manifest! Come forth, onmyo!
Feast your eyes, folks! It's an onmyodo\ntechnique! And it's hit home with explosive\nforce! Elisanne is flying clear out of—
Out of bounds!\nThe winner is...Namel—er, Lord Seimei!
YEAAAAAAH! SEI! MEI! SEI! MEI! SEI! MEI!
Yes... But I suppose I lost, then?
Fraid so. Why didn't you do anything at the\nend there? You totally could have stopped\nthat.
When I heard that mirror was a keepsake\nof his late grandfather, I...
The thought of taking it from him rattled\nme. I can empathize with the pain of\nlosing something I want to protect.
Then tell your empathy to stuff it!\nHow is that any different than the\nposition you and I are in?
You're right, of course. It was a moment's\nweakness unbefitting a Paladyn, and it's\ncost me my promise to the children.
I'll still do all I can to aid in bolstering the\norphanage's finances, obviously, but for\nnow, I need to think of how to apologize.
Nah. I don't think there's any need for\nthat just yet.
You exposed Nameless's identity.\nAnd now we know he's using onmyodo.

That means we can come up with a
countermeasure. If it helps me win,
then boom. We'll split the prize, and
everybody's problems'll be solved.
Course I would! C'mon, we're friends.\nWe help each other out all the time!
Just you wait, Seimei. Now I'm fighting\nfor TWO worthy causes. I'm winning\nthis tourney, no matter what it takes!
